-Thanks, Ardelia.

256
00:21:39,674 --> 00:21:41,300
-Starling?
-Sir?

257
00:21:42,302 --> 00:21:43,760
Miggs is dead.

258
00:21:44,888 --> 00:21:47,514
Dead? How?

259
00:21:48,475 --> 00:21:51,977
The orderly heard Lecter whispering
to him all afternoon, and Miggs crying.

260
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:55,731
They found him at bed check.
He'd swallowed his own tongue.

261
00:21:57,609 --> 00:21:58,901
Starling?

262
00:21:59,235 --> 00:22:01,236
Yeah, I'm still here, sir.

263
00:22:01,321 --> 00:22:04,281
I just... I don't know
how to feel about this.

264
00:22:04,741 --> 00:22:09,077
You don't have to feel any way about it.
Lecter did it to amuse himself.

265
00:22:09,537 --> 00:22:11,830
Look, I know it got ugly today,

266
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:15,250
but you mentioned a name
at the end. Mofet.

267
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:17,211
Any follow-up on her?

268
00:22:17,962 --> 00:22:20,756
Well, Lecter altered or destroyed
most of his patients' histories

269
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:23,425
prior to capture, so there's no record
of anyone named Mofet.

270
00:22:23,468 --> 00:22:27,721
But I thought the "yourself" reference

271
00:22:27,764 --> 00:22:29,389
was too hokey for Lecter,

272
00:22:29,432 --> 00:22:33,769
so I figured, he's from Baltimore,
and I looked in the phone book,

273
00:22:33,811 --> 00:22:37,314
and there's a "Your Self Storage" facility,

274
00:22:37,398 --> 00:22:39,650
right outside of downtown Baltimore, sir.

275
00:22:41,945 --> 00:22:45,739
Unit 31 was leased for 10 years,

276
00:22:45,949 --> 00:22:47,533
prepaid in full.

277
00:22:47,784 --> 00:22:49,034
The contract

278
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:53,121
is in the name of a Miss Hester Mofet.

279
00:22:53,998 --> 00:22:56,500
So nobody's been in here since 1980?

280
00:22:56,793 --> 00:22:58,544
Not to my knowledge.

281
00:22:59,254 --> 00:23:03,090
Privacy is a great concern
to my customers.

282
00:23:03,675 --> 00:23:05,884
Yes, I won't disturb anything. I promise.

283
00:23:05,969 --> 00:23:08,428
I'll be out of here before you know it.

284
00:23:08,471 --> 00:23:12,099
-Can I help you?
-Yes, actually, you can.

285
00:23:17,188 --> 00:23:18,480
It's stuck.

286
00:23:18,523 --> 00:23:21,275
We could return tomorrow with my son.

287
00:23:21,484 --> 00:23:22,985
What about him?

288
00:23:24,362 --> 00:23:29,116
I would ask my driver to help you,
but he detests physical labor.

289
00:23:30,034 --> 00:23:31,159
Great.

290
00:23:31,786 --> 00:23:34,788
You just stay here.
I'll be back in one minute.

291
00:24:07,030 --> 00:24:08,322
It's stuck.

292
00:24:08,364 --> 00:24:10,490
Hand me that flashlight, sir.

293
00:24:21,169 --> 00:24:22,210
Oh.

294
00:24:24,047 --> 00:24:28,383
If this door should fall down
or anything else,

295
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:32,846
this is the number
for our Baltimore field office.

296
00:24:32,889 --> 00:24:34,723
Now, they know that you're with me.

297
00:24:34,807 --> 00:24:36,892
You call them if anything should happen.

298
00:24:36,934 --> 00:24:38,560
Yes, Miss Starling.

299
00:27:10,046 --> 00:27:11,046
Clarice...

300
00:27:11,297 --> 00:27:14,257
-They're waiting for you. Watch yourself.
-Thank you.

301
00:27:15,176 --> 00:27:18,470
Hester Mofet.
It's an anagram, isn't it, Doctor?

302
00:27:19,388 --> 00:27:22,724
Hester Mofet, "The rest of me."

303
00:27:22,767 --> 00:27:26,436
"Miss The Rest Of Me,"
meaning that you rented that garage?

304
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:03,890
Thank you.

305
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:06,476
Your bleeding has stopped.

306
00:28:08,604 --> 00:28:10,105
How did you...

307
00:28:11,774 --> 00:28:13,233
It's nothing.

308
00:28:13,609 --> 00:28:15,318
It's just a scratch.

309
00:28:16,612 --> 00:28:19,030
Dr. Lecter, whose head is in that bottle?

310
00:28:19,115 --> 00:28:22,284
Why don't you ask me about Buffalo Bill?

311
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:24,369
Why, do you know something about him?

312
00:28:24,453 --> 00:28:26,580
I might, if I saw the case file.

313
00:28:26,622 --> 00:28:28,582
You could get that for me.

314
00:28:28,624 --> 00:28:30,292
Why don't we talk about Miss Mofet?

315
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:32,335
You wanted me to find him.

316
00:28:32,753 --> 00:28:35,964
His real name is Benjamin Raspail.

317
00:28:36,465 --> 00:28:38,258
A former patient of mine,

318
00:28:38,301 --> 00:28:42,804
whose romantic attachments ran to,
shall we say, the exotic.

319
00:28:43,472 --> 00:28:44,973
I did not kill him, I assure you.

320
00:28:45,057 --> 00:28:47,767
Merely tucked him away
very much as I found him,

321
00:28:47,810 --> 00:28:50,353
after he'd missed three appointments.

322
00:28:51,522 --> 00:28:53,857
If you didn't kill him, then who did, sir?

323
00:28:53,941 --> 00:28:55,233
Who can say?

324
00:28:55,318 --> 00:28:56,985
Best thing for him, really.

325
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:59,279
His therapy was going nowhere.

326
00:28:59,989 --> 00:29:02,824
His dress, makeup...

327
00:29:03,492 --> 00:29:05,285
Raspail was a transvestite?

328
00:29:05,328 --> 00:29:07,746
In life? Oh, no.

329
00:29:07,830 --> 00:29:10,165
Garden variety manic-depressive.

330
00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:12,292
Tedious. Very tedious.

331
00:29:12,835 --> 00:29:15,420
And I just think of him
as a kind of experiment,

332
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:18,882
a fledgling killer's first effort
at transformation.

333
00:29:19,091 --> 00:29:21,843
How did you feel
when you saw him, Clarice?

334
00:29:22,428 --> 00:29:24,346
Scared at first, then,

335
00:29:25,348 --> 00:29:26,681
exhilarated.

336
00:29:27,308 --> 00:29:29,643
Jack Crawford is helping your career,
isn't he?

337
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:32,771
Apparently, he likes you,
and you like him, too.

338
00:29:33,189 --> 00:29:35,065
I never thought about it.

339
00:29:35,358 --> 00:29:38,318
Do you think Jack Crawford
wants you sexually?

340
00:29:38,402 --> 00:29:39,945
True, he is much older,

341
00:29:40,029 --> 00:29:43,657
but do you think he visualizes
scenarios, exchanges,

342
00:29:43,699 --> 00:29:45,075
fucking you?

343
00:29:47,870 --> 00:29:49,371
That doesn't interest me, Doctor.

344
00:29:49,413 --> 00:29:52,999
Frankly, it's the sort of thing
that Miggs would say.

345
00:29:54,961 --> 00:29:56,378
Not anymore.

346
00:30:04,136 --> 00:30:05,720
Thank you, Barney.

347
00:30:09,725 --> 00:30:11,977
What happened to your drawings?

348
00:30:13,354 --> 00:30:15,605
Punishment, you see, for Miggs.

349
00:30:16,065 --> 00:30:17,941
Just like that gospel program.

350
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:21,069
When you leave,
they'll turn the volume way up.

351
00:30:21,153 --> 00:30:24,197
Dr. Chilton does enjoy his petty torments.

352
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:27,867
What did you mean
by transformation, Doctor?

353
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:39,754
I've been in this room
for eight years now, Clarice.

354
00:30:40,214 --> 00:30:43,633
I know they will never,
ever let me out while I'm alive.

355
00:30:44,427 --> 00:30:46,261
What I want is a view.

356
00:30:46,762 --> 00:30:50,598
I want a window where I can see a tree,
or even water.

357
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:54,269
I want to be in a federal institution
far away from Dr. Chilton.

358
00:30:54,353 --> 00:30:56,896
What did you mean by fledgling killer?

359
00:30:57,189 --> 00:30:59,274
Are you saying that he's killed again?

360
00:30:59,316 --> 00:31:02,610
I'm offering you a psychological profile
on Buffalo Bill,

361
00:31:02,695 --> 00:31:04,738
based on the case evidence.

362
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:12,579
I'll help you catch him, Clarice.

363
00:31:19,336 --> 00:31:21,463
You know who he is, don't you?

364
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:25,133
Tell me who decapitated
your patient, Doctor.

365
00:31:25,217 --> 00:31:27,927
All good things to those who wait.

366
00:31:28,471 --> 00:31:29,763
I've waited, Clarice,

367
00:31:29,805 --> 00:31:32,682
but how long can you
and old Jackie boy wait?

368
00:31:33,142 --> 00:31:35,143
Our little Billy must already be searching

369
00:31:35,186 --> 00:31:38,271
for that next special lady.

370
00:32:41,544 --> 00:32:43,294
Hey, little cheeper.

371
00:32:52,012 --> 00:32:53,721
I'll be right there.

372
00:32:54,515 --> 00:32:55,682
Oh, shoot.

373
00:33:02,731 --> 00:33:03,982
Goddamn it.

374
00:33:13,159 --> 00:33:14,617
Perfect! Jesus.

375
00:33:20,457 --> 00:33:22,208
Can I help you with that?

376
00:33:23,294 --> 00:33:25,336
-Would you?
-Sure.

377
00:33:26,422 --> 00:33:28,089
-Thank you.
-That's all right.

378
00:33:28,174 --> 00:33:30,550
-You look kind of handicapped.
-Yeah.

379
00:33:30,885 --> 00:33:33,887
I got it this far.
I just can't get it up in the truck.

380
00:33:33,929 --> 00:33:35,471
Here. Just grab this.

381
00:33:36,015 --> 00:33:37,056
Okay.

382
00:33:37,099 --> 00:33:39,267
Good. Just set it down. That's good.

383
00:33:40,019 --> 00:33:43,271
Get in the truck.
I want to push it all the way up.

384
00:33:44,023 --> 00:33:46,024
-I really appreciate this. Thank you.
-All right.

385
00:33:46,108 --> 00:33:47,692
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

386
00:33:48,319 --> 00:33:50,278
Just go all the way back.

387
00:33:51,113 --> 00:33:52,947
Okay. Is this good?

388
00:33:53,032 --> 00:33:54,532
Yeah, that's good.

389
00:33:56,410 --> 00:33:58,578
-That's great.
-Okay.

390
00:33:59,079 --> 00:34:01,414
Say, are you about a size 14?

391
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:02,749
Sorry?

392
00:34:24,146 --> 00:34:25,146
Good.

393
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:47,293
Oh, good. Good.

394
00:35:03,269 --> 00:35:04,394
Hold!

395
00:35:16,991 --> 00:35:18,199
Starling!

396
00:35:20,911 --> 00:35:22,620
Outside. Let's go.

397
00:35:23,831 --> 00:35:26,708
Cindy, in the ring for Starling. Let's go!

398
00:35:35,092 --> 00:35:36,968
FBI! Hold it! Hold it right there!

399
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:38,761
Saddle up. Pack your field gear.
You're moving out.

400
00:35:38,846 --> 00:35:40,263
-You're going with Crawford.
-Where?

401
00:35:40,347 --> 00:35:42,056
Found a girl's body down in West Virginia.

402
00:35:42,141 --> 00:35:45,059
Been in the water about a week.
Looks like a Buffalo Bill-type situation.

403
00:35:56,989 --> 00:36:00,116
He keeps them alive for three days.
We don't know why.

404
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:03,369
There's no evidence
of rape or physical abuse prior to death.

405
00:36:03,412 --> 00:36:06,456
All the mutilation you see there
is postmortem.

406
00:36:06,832 --> 00:36:08,499
Okay, three days.

407
00:36:08,584 --> 00:36:12,253
Then he shoots them, skins them,
and dumps them.

408
00:36:12,546 --> 00:36:14,339
Each body in a different river.

409
00:36:14,423 --> 00:36:17,592
The water leaves us no trace evidence
of any kind.

410
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:20,303
That's Fredrica Bimmel, the first one.

411
00:36:20,387 --> 00:36:23,389
Her body was the only one
he took the trouble to weight down,

412
00:36:23,432 --> 00:36:26,184
so actually, she was the third girl found.

413
00:36:26,435 --> 00:36:28,269
After her, he got lazy.

414
00:36:30,647 --> 00:36:33,107
Okay. Let's see.

415
00:36:33,776 --> 00:36:35,777
Circles where the girls were abducted,

416
00:36:35,819 --> 00:36:38,112
arrows where their bodies were found.

417
00:36:38,197 --> 00:36:41,366
This new one today washed up here.

418
00:36:41,450 --> 00:36:42,909
Elk River, West Virginia.

419
00:37:02,596 --> 00:37:05,473
Look at him, Starling.
Tell me what you see.

420
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:07,975
Well, he's a white male.

421
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:11,729
Serial killers tend to hunt
within their own ethnic groups.

422
00:37:11,814 --> 00:37:12,855
He's not a drifter.

423
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:16,484
He's got his own house somewhere,
not an apartment.

424
00:37:16,819 --> 00:37:19,821
-Why?
-What he does with them takes privacy.

425
00:37:20,322 --> 00:37:22,365
He's in his 30s or 40s.

426
00:37:22,449 --> 00:37:24,742
He's got real physical strength,

427
00:37:24,993 --> 00:37:27,829
combined with an older man's self-control.

428
00:37:27,913 --> 00:37:30,164
He's cautious, precise.

429
00:37:30,999 --> 00:37:33,835
And he's never impulsive. He'll never stop.

430
00:37:34,211 --> 00:37:35,461
Why not?

431
00:37:37,089 --> 00:37:40,675
He's got a real taste for it now.
He's getting better at his work.

432
00:37:42,261 --> 00:37:44,011
Not bad, Starling.

433
00:37:44,096 --> 00:37:46,389
-Questions?
-Yes, sir.

434
00:37:47,266 --> 00:37:50,852
You haven't mentioned anything about
the information contained in my report

435
00:37:50,894 --> 00:37:53,020
or Dr. Lecter's offer, sir.

436
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:54,856
I'm considering it.

437
00:37:55,023 --> 00:37:57,900
That's why you sent me in there, isn't it?

438
00:37:57,985 --> 00:38:00,153
To get his help on Buffalo Bill, sir?

439
00:38:03,198 --> 00:38:06,033
Well, if that was the case, then I just...

440
00:38:06,410 --> 00:38:08,828
I just wish I was in on it. That's all.

441
00:38:09,079 --> 00:38:11,372
If I had sent you in there
with an actual agenda,

442
00:38:11,457 --> 00:38:13,332
Lecter would have known it instantly.

443
00:38:13,375 --> 00:38:16,711
He would have toyed with you,
then turned to stone.

444
00:38:50,412 --> 00:38:53,748
Excuse me.
Sheriff Perkins, these are the FBI people.

445
00:38:53,916 --> 00:38:56,501
Sheriff Perkins. Jack Crawford, FBI.

446
00:38:56,835 --> 00:38:59,420
Special Agent Terry, Agent Starling.

447
00:38:59,630 --> 00:39:02,089
We appreciate being invited
to your jurisdiction.

448
00:39:02,257 --> 00:39:05,468
I didn't call you. That was somebody
from the State Attorney's office.

449
00:39:05,552 --> 00:39:07,720
We'll extend you every courtesy,
but right now...

450
00:39:07,763 --> 00:39:12,225
Sheriff, this type of sex crime
has certain aspects.

451
00:39:12,267 --> 00:39:14,602
I'd just as soon discuss in private.

452
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:16,479
You know what I mean?

453
00:41:07,174 --> 00:41:09,759
-Oscar, fetch Dr. Akin from the chapel.
-Yes, sir.

454
00:41:09,843 --> 00:41:11,052
Starling, we're back here.

455
00:41:11,136 --> 00:41:14,263
Tell Lamar to come on
when he's finished playing his music.

456
00:41:14,431 --> 00:41:14,555
Yeah. We'll be sending in a minute.

457
00:41:14,556 --> 00:41:16,974
Yeah. We'll be sending in a minute.

458
00:41:17,726 --> 00:41:18,934
Is this working?

459
00:41:19,019 --> 00:41:21,729
I need a six-way linkup.

460
00:41:21,772 --> 00:41:23,481
Chicago, Detroit...

461
00:41:23,565 --> 00:41:24,940
What? What?

462
00:41:30,155 --> 00:41:32,865
Excuse me! Excuse me, gentlemen.

463
00:41:32,908 --> 00:41:35,201
You officers and gentlemen,
listen here now.

464
00:41:35,243 --> 00:41:36,869
There's things we need to do for her.

465
00:41:36,912 --> 00:41:38,788
I know that you all brought her this far

466
00:41:38,872 --> 00:41:41,540
and that her folks would
thank you if they could

467
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:43,918
for your kindness and your sensitivity.

468
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:47,421
And now, please,
go on now and let us take care of her.

469
00:41:48,131 --> 00:41:49,507
Go on, now.

470
00:41:52,594 --> 00:41:53,928
Thank you.

471
00:41:57,641 --> 00:41:59,016
Thank you.

472
00:42:00,769 --> 00:42:02,186
Okay, good.

473
00:42:10,445 --> 00:42:13,155
Yeah, that's right. West Virginia. Elk River.

474
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:15,282
Stand by for transmission.

475
00:42:19,121 --> 00:42:20,246
Ray.

476
00:42:32,676 --> 00:42:35,428
Doctor, Lamar, let's take a look at her.

477
00:42:51,945 --> 00:42:53,279
Oh, Jesus.

478
00:43:01,037 --> 00:43:02,621
Okay, Starling.

479
00:43:07,669 --> 00:43:08,794
Bill.

480
00:43:24,853 --> 00:43:29,315
Star-shaped contact entrance wound
over the sternum.

481
00:43:31,526 --> 00:43:33,652
Muzzle stamp at the top.

482
00:43:33,695 --> 00:43:36,155
-Wrongful death.
-"Wrongful death."

483
00:43:37,032 --> 00:43:40,367
She'll have to go
to the state pathologist at Claxton.

484
00:43:40,452 --> 00:43:42,745
Well, I better get back to that service.

485
00:43:42,829 --> 00:43:44,580
Lamar will help you.

486
00:43:44,873 --> 00:43:46,415
Lord Almighty.

487
00:43:50,879 --> 00:43:53,214
What else do you see, Starling?

488
00:43:54,174 --> 00:43:56,467
Well, she's not local.

489
00:43:57,761 --> 00:44:00,888
Her ears are pierced three times,
and there's...

490
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:05,226
Glitter nail polish. It looks like town to me.

491
00:44:10,899 --> 00:44:12,608
Two of her fingernails are broken off,

492
00:44:12,692 --> 00:44:16,237
and there's dirt or grit under them.

493
00:44:16,905 --> 00:44:20,491
It looks like she's tried to claw her way
through something.

494
00:44:20,575 --> 00:44:23,410
Ray, get pictures of her teeth.
We'll fax them through Missing Persons.

495
00:44:23,453 --> 00:44:24,620
Right.

496
00:44:34,422 --> 00:44:36,090
Let's do another.

497
00:44:44,850 --> 00:44:47,309
She's got something in her throat.

498
00:44:47,853 --> 00:44:49,770
When a body comes out of the water,

499
00:44:49,813 --> 00:44:52,940
lots of times there's, like,
leaves and things in the mouth.

500
00:45:24,139 --> 00:45:26,974
What is that, some kind of seedpod?

501
00:45:27,767 --> 00:45:30,185
No, sir. That's a bug cocoon.

502
00:45:30,854 --> 00:45:33,689
There's no way that could get
way down in there like that.

503
00:45:33,773 --> 00:45:36,483
Not unless somebody shoved it in there.

504
00:45:38,778 --> 00:45:41,322
She'll be easier to print
when we turn her over.

505
00:45:41,406 --> 00:45:44,700
-Lamar, will you give me a hand with this?
-Yes, sir, I will.

506
00:45:48,496 --> 00:45:52,041
Oh, Jack. What do you make of these?

507
00:45:52,500 --> 00:45:54,585
Different configuration
than the other victims.

508
00:45:54,669 --> 00:45:55,961
Get close-ups.

509
00:45:56,004 --> 00:45:59,673
