Here, sir. Use mine.

757
01:02:43,844 --> 01:02:47,680
Senator Martin, Dr. Hannibal Lecter.

758
01:02:53,020 --> 01:02:54,395
Dr. Lecter,

759
01:02:55,064 --> 01:02:58,399
I brought an affidavit
guaranteeing your new rights.

760
01:02:58,734 --> 01:03:01,361
You'll want to read it before I sign.

761
01:03:04,907 --> 01:03:09,369
I won't waste your time or Catherine's
time bargaining for petty privileges.

762
01:03:09,411 --> 01:03:11,537
Clarice Starling
and that awful Jack Crawford

763
01:03:11,580 --> 01:03:13,706
have wasted far too much time already.

764
01:03:13,791 --> 01:03:16,834
I only pray they haven't doomed
the poor girl.

765
01:03:17,920 --> 01:03:21,547
Let me help you now
and I will trust you when it is all over.

766
01:03:21,632 --> 01:03:23,549
You have my word. Paul?

767
01:03:26,053 --> 01:03:28,888
Buffalo Bill's real name is Louis Friend.

768
01:03:30,182 --> 01:03:31,224
I met him just once.

769
01:03:31,308 --> 01:03:34,394
He was referred to me in April
or May, 1980,

770
01:03:34,436 --> 01:03:36,771
by my patient Benjamin Raspail.

771
01:03:37,314 --> 01:03:39,399
They were lovers, you see.

772
01:03:39,566 --> 01:03:42,986
But Raspail had become very frightened.

773
01:03:43,779 --> 01:03:46,990
Apparently, Louis had murdered
a transient

774
01:03:47,408 --> 01:03:50,535
and done things with her skin.

775
01:03:51,578 --> 01:03:54,664
We need his address
and a physical description.

776
01:03:55,666 --> 01:03:57,333
Tell me, Senator.

777
01:03:57,960 --> 01:04:00,420
Did you nurse Catherine yourself?

778
01:04:00,838 --> 01:04:03,172
-What?
-Did you breast-feed her?

779
01:04:03,257 --> 01:04:05,883
-Now, wait a minute!
-Yes, I did.

780
01:04:06,301 --> 01:04:09,929
-Toughened your nipples, didn't it?
-You son of a bitch!

781
01:04:10,180 --> 01:04:13,766
Amputate a man's leg,
and he can still feel it tickling.

782
01:04:14,143 --> 01:04:17,645
Tell me, Mom,
when your little girl is on the slab,

783
01:04:17,730 --> 01:04:19,731
where will it tickle you?

784
01:04:19,773 --> 01:04:22,775
Take this thing back to Baltimore.

785
01:04:24,278 --> 01:04:27,405
Five-foot-ten, strongly built,
about 180 pounds.

786
01:04:27,531 --> 01:04:29,782
Hair, blond. Eyes, pale blue.

787
01:04:30,284 --> 01:04:31,576
He'd be about 35 now.

788
01:04:31,618 --> 01:04:34,704
He said he lived in Philadelphia,
but may have lied.

789
01:04:34,788 --> 01:04:36,789
That's all I can remember, Mom.

790
01:04:36,832 --> 01:04:39,959
But if I think of any more,
I will let you know.

791
01:04:42,004 --> 01:04:44,464
Oh, and, Senator, just one more thing.

792
01:04:46,800 --> 01:04:48,342
Love your suit.

793
01:04:50,596 --> 01:04:52,805
I tell you now
that in a meeting earlier this evening

794
01:04:52,848 --> 01:04:54,140
with Senator Ruth Martin,

795
01:04:54,183 --> 01:04:57,226
Dr. Lecter agreed
to assist in the investigation

796
01:04:57,311 --> 01:05:00,146
of trying to find the abductor
of Catherine Martin, Buffalo Bill.

797
01:05:00,189 --> 01:05:01,230
How do you fit in, sir?

798
01:05:01,315 --> 01:05:02,815
Well, it's only through
my own unique insight

799
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:04,942
into Lecter's mind
that this breakthrough was possible.

800
01:05:04,985 --> 01:05:06,110
And Buffalo Bill's real name...

801
01:05:06,153 --> 01:05:10,073
Buffalo Bill's real name is now a matter
of record with the proper authorities.

802
01:05:10,157 --> 01:05:12,742
-Can you give us any more information?
-My name is Dr. Frederick Chilton.

803
01:05:12,826 --> 01:05:14,327
-How do you spell that?
-C-H...

804
01:05:15,913 --> 01:05:20,500
-Are you with Dr. Chilton's group?
-Oh, well, I just saw him outside, sir.

805
01:05:20,834 --> 01:05:24,295
Access to Lecter is strictly limited.
We've been getting death threats.

806
01:05:24,338 --> 01:05:26,047
I understand, sir.

807
01:05:32,137 --> 01:05:34,180
Log in. Check your weapon.

808
01:05:35,015 --> 01:05:37,433
Well, I can't take all the credit for myself.

809
01:05:37,518 --> 01:05:40,061
Senator Martin, the Justice Department,
the people at the FBI,

810
01:05:40,145 --> 01:05:42,355
the folks at the Baltimore State Hospital.

811
01:05:42,397 --> 01:05:45,733
And now for the hard part,
apprehending the suspect.

812
01:05:45,984 --> 01:05:48,444
Excuse me, folks,
I'm gonna have to catch a flight.

813
01:05:52,366 --> 01:05:54,575
Command desk. Officer Jacobs.

814
01:06:03,210 --> 01:06:05,336
Is it true what they're saying?

815
01:06:07,381 --> 01:06:09,465
He's some kind of vampire?

816
01:06:11,802 --> 01:06:14,470
They don't have a name for what he is.

817
01:06:15,139 --> 01:06:17,014
You do know the rules, ma'am?

818
01:06:17,516 --> 01:06:20,101
Yes, Lieutenant Boyle.
I've questioned him before.

819
01:06:23,438 --> 01:06:24,730
Go ahead.

820
01:07:01,643 --> 01:07:03,561
Good evening, Clarice.

821
01:07:05,230 --> 01:07:08,566
I thought you might like
your drawings back, Doctor.

822
01:07:10,652 --> 01:07:12,904
Just until you get your view.

823
01:07:13,405 --> 01:07:15,198
How very thoughtful.

824
01:07:16,617 --> 01:07:19,702
Or did Jack Crawford send you
for one last wheedle

825
01:07:19,786 --> 01:07:21,996
before you're both booted off the case?

826
01:07:22,414 --> 01:07:24,749
No. I came because I wanted to.

827
01:07:29,296 --> 01:07:31,589
People will say we're in love.

828
01:07:35,844 --> 01:07:37,929
Anthrax Island.

829
01:07:38,597 --> 01:07:41,515
That was an especially nice touch, Clarice.

830
01:07:41,767 --> 01:07:44,018
-Yours?
-Yes.

831
01:07:44,937 --> 01:07:48,064
Yeah! That was good.

832
01:07:48,982 --> 01:07:50,983
Pity about poor Catherine, though.

833
01:07:53,528 --> 01:07:55,988
Your anagrams are showing, Doctor.

834
01:07:56,907 --> 01:07:58,407
Louis Friend?

835
01:07:59,159 --> 01:08:02,119
Iron sulfide, also known as Fool's Gold.

836
01:08:02,746 --> 01:08:06,832
Oh, Clarice. Your problem is
you need to get more fun out of life.

837
01:08:07,125 --> 01:08:10,086
You were telling me the truth
back in Baltimore, sir.

838
01:08:10,170 --> 01:08:11,963
Please continue now.

839
01:08:12,256 --> 01:08:15,174
Well, I have read the case files, have you?

840
01:08:15,217 --> 01:08:18,386
Everything you need to find him
is right there in those pages.

841
01:08:18,470 --> 01:08:22,890
-Then tell me how.
-First principles, Clarice. Simplicity.

842
01:08:23,433 --> 01:08:24,934
Read Marcus Aurelius.

843
01:08:25,018 --> 01:08:28,312
Of each particular thing,
ask what is it in itself?

844
01:08:28,522 --> 01:08:30,314
What is its nature?

845
01:08:30,732 --> 01:08:34,026
What does he do, this man you seek?

846
01:08:36,196 --> 01:08:37,738
He kills women.

847
01:08:37,823 --> 01:08:40,366
No! That is incidental.

848
01:08:41,535 --> 01:08:43,369
What is the first
and principal thing he does?

849
01:08:43,412 --> 01:08:46,706
What needs does he serve by killing?

850
01:08:47,207 --> 01:08:48,416
Anger.

851
01:08:50,127 --> 01:08:54,505
Social acceptance
and sexual frustrations...

852
01:08:54,548 --> 01:08:57,508
No! He covets.

853
01:08:58,802 --> 01:09:00,553
That is his nature.

854
01:09:00,887 --> 01:09:03,556
And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?

855
01:09:04,057 --> 01:09:06,392
Do we seek out things to covet?

856
01:09:07,227 --> 01:09:09,270
Make an effort to answer now.

857
01:09:09,354 --> 01:09:11,605
No. We just...

858
01:09:12,065 --> 01:09:15,151
No. We begin by coveting
what we see every day.

859
01:09:15,485 --> 01:09:18,779
Don't you feel eyes
moving over your body, Clarice?

860
01:09:19,656 --> 01:09:22,867
And don't your eyes
seek out the things you want?

861
01:09:23,577 --> 01:09:26,037
All right. Yes. Now please tell me how.

862
01:09:26,413 --> 01:09:30,249
No. It is your turn to tell me, Clarice.

863
01:09:30,500 --> 01:09:33,377
You don't have any more vacations to sell.

864
01:09:33,754 --> 01:09:35,963
Why did you leave that ranch?

865
01:09:36,506 --> 01:09:40,217
Doctor, we don't have any more time
for any of this now.

866
01:09:40,719 --> 01:09:43,387
But we don't reckon time the same way,
do we, Clarice?

867
01:09:43,430 --> 01:09:45,389
This is all the time you'll ever have.

868
01:09:45,432 --> 01:09:47,933
Later. Now, please, listen to me.
We've only got five...

869
01:09:47,976 --> 01:09:50,561
No! I will listen now.

870
01:09:53,565 --> 01:09:55,441
After your father's murder,
you were orphaned.

871
01:09:55,484 --> 01:09:56,734
You were ten years old.

872
01:09:56,777 --> 01:10:00,613
You went to live with cousins
on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.

873
01:10:00,655 --> 01:10:01,781
And?

874
01:10:03,909 --> 01:10:06,077
And one morning, I just ran away.

875
01:10:06,787 --> 01:10:09,830
Not "just", Clarice. What set you off?

876
01:10:10,624 --> 01:10:14,043
-You started at what time?
-Early. Still dark.

877
01:10:14,419 --> 01:10:18,422
Then something woke you, didn't it?
Was it a dream? What was it?

878
01:10:19,800 --> 01:10:21,801
I heard a strange noise.

879
01:10:22,719 --> 01:10:24,136
What was it?

880
01:10:24,721 --> 01:10:28,224
It was screaming.

881
01:10:30,143 --> 01:10:33,145
Some kind of screaming,
like a child's voice.

882
01:10:33,522 --> 01:10:35,147
What did you do?

883
01:10:35,524 --> 01:10:39,068
I went downstairs, outside.

884
01:10:41,905 --> 01:10:43,948
I crept up into the barn.

885
01:10:44,658 --> 01:10:47,701
I was so scared to look inside, but I had to.

886
01:10:48,912 --> 01:10:52,039
And what did you see, Clarice?
What did you see?

887
01:10:53,792 --> 01:10:57,336
Lambs. They were screaming.

888
01:10:58,505 --> 01:11:01,257
They were slaughtering the spring lambs?

889
01:11:01,675 --> 01:11:03,676
And they were screaming.

890
01:11:04,886 --> 01:11:07,388
-And you ran away?
-No.

891
01:11:08,598 --> 01:11:10,724
First I tried to free them.

892
01:11:11,268 --> 01:11:13,727
I opened the gate to their pen,
but they wouldn't run.

893
01:11:13,812 --> 01:11:17,106
They just stood there, confused.
They wouldn't run.

894
01:11:17,524 --> 01:11:20,192
But you could and you did, didn't you?

895
01:11:20,861 --> 01:11:24,363
Yes. I took one lamb,
and I ran away as fast as I could.

896
01:11:24,448 --> 01:11:27,032
-Where were you going, Clarice?
-I don't know.

897
01:11:27,117 --> 01:11:31,829
I didn't have any food, any water,
and it was very cold, very cold.

898
01:11:34,499 --> 01:11:38,544
I thought if I could save just one, but,

899
01:11:41,131 --> 01:11:42,756
he was so heavy.

900
01:11:43,758 --> 01:11:45,384
He was so heavy.

901
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:55,019
I didn't get more than a few miles
when the sheriff's car picked me up.

902
01:11:57,731 --> 01:11:59,064
The rancher was so angry,

903
01:11:59,107 --> 01:12:02,610
he sent me to live
at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.

904
01:12:02,694 --> 01:12:04,904
I never saw the ranch again.

905
01:12:05,489 --> 01:12:07,948
What became of your lamb, Clarice?

906
01:12:10,160 --> 01:12:11,785
They killed him.

907
01:12:11,870 --> 01:12:14,246
You still wake up sometimes, don't you?

908
01:12:14,331 --> 01:12:18,918
Wake up in the dark
and hear the screaming of the lambs.

909
01:12:19,961 --> 01:12:21,086
Yes.

910
01:12:22,797 --> 01:12:27,092
And you think if you save poor Catherine,
you could make them stop, don't you?

911
01:12:27,177 --> 01:12:29,553
You think if Catherine lives,

912
01:12:29,596 --> 01:12:32,389
you won't wake up in the dark ever again

913
01:12:32,891 --> 01:12:35,518
to that awful screaming of the lambs.

914
01:12:36,895 --> 01:12:39,855
I don't know. I don't know.

915
01:12:42,067 --> 01:12:45,694
Thank you, Clarice. Thank you.

916
01:12:46,571 --> 01:12:48,614
Tell me his name, Doctor.

917
01:12:55,539 --> 01:12:57,456
Dr. Chilton, I presume.

918
01:12:58,333 --> 01:13:00,501
I think you know each other.

919
01:13:02,128 --> 01:13:03,462
Okay.

920
01:13:04,464 --> 01:13:06,465
-We found her.
-Let's go!

921
01:13:06,716 --> 01:13:08,634
It's your turn, Doctor.

922
01:13:08,885 --> 01:13:10,886
-Out.
-Tell me his name.

923
01:13:10,971 --> 01:13:13,639
Sorry, ma'am, I've got orders.
I have to put you on a plane.

924
01:13:13,723 --> 01:13:15,140
Come on now.

925
01:13:15,183 --> 01:13:16,725
Brave Clarice.

926
01:13:17,394 --> 01:13:21,188
You will let me know when
those lambs stop screaming, won't you?

927
01:13:21,273 --> 01:13:23,274
Tell me his name, Doctor!

928
01:13:23,316 --> 01:13:24,608
Clarice!

929
01:13:25,944 --> 01:13:27,486
Your case file.

930
01:13:32,701 --> 01:13:34,410
Goodbye, Clarice.

931
01:14:40,226 --> 01:14:42,227
Ready when you are, Doc.

932
01:14:42,395 --> 01:14:44,563
Just another minute, please.

933
01:14:53,531 --> 01:14:55,949
The son of a bitch
demanded a second dinner.

934
01:14:56,034 --> 01:14:58,077
Lamb chops, extra rare.

935
01:14:58,119 --> 01:15:00,079
Wonder what he wants for breakfast.

936
01:15:00,121 --> 01:15:02,414
Some damn thing from the zoo?

937
01:15:24,229 --> 01:15:26,021
Good evening, gentlemen.

938
01:15:26,106 --> 01:15:29,608
-Okay, Doc. Grab some floor.
-Same drill as before, please.

939
01:15:37,200 --> 01:15:39,743
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

940
01:15:55,969 --> 01:15:57,094
Okay.

941
01:16:03,977 --> 01:16:05,978
Hand me that, would you?

942
01:16:11,151 --> 01:16:12,359
Thanks.

943
01:16:16,197 --> 01:16:18,282
Mind the drawings, please.

944
01:16:21,327 --> 01:16:22,661
Thank you.

945
01:16:47,061 --> 01:16:49,354
-Jimmy, watch it! He's got me!
-Jesus, Bill!

946
01:16:56,362 --> 01:16:57,863
Jesus Christ!

947
01:18:16,442 --> 01:18:19,027
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

948
01:18:28,288 --> 01:18:29,955
What is this shit?

949
01:18:32,750 --> 01:18:36,461
-Did somebody go up on five?
-No. Nobody went up.

950
01:18:36,796 --> 01:18:38,714
Call Pembry. Ask him...

951
01:18:41,342 --> 01:18:44,094
CP, shots fired on five. Repeat.

952
01:18:44,470 --> 01:18:47,014
-Shots fired on five.
-Sergeant Tate.

953
01:18:49,767 --> 01:18:51,101
Holy shit.

954
01:18:51,144 --> 01:18:52,978
What the hell? Bitch!

955
01:18:53,521 --> 01:18:54,771
Shut up.

956
01:18:55,064 --> 01:18:57,608
-Bobby, get the vest.
-Right, Sarge.

957
01:18:58,276 --> 01:19:00,152
-Brady, Howard...
-Look!

958
01:19:03,323 --> 01:19:04,698
It stopped.

959
01:19:06,200 --> 01:19:07,910
Seal off a 10 block radius.

960
01:19:07,994 --> 01:19:10,829
Get me the SWAT team
and an ambulance double-quick.

961
01:19:10,872 --> 01:19:12,080
We're going up.

962
01:19:41,194 --> 01:19:42,819
Pembry!

963
01:19:44,322 --> 01:19:46,031
Boyle!

964
01:19:58,711 --> 01:19:59,920
Oh, God!

965
01:20:07,220 --> 01:20:08,220
Go.

966
01:20:16,062 --> 01:20:17,521
-Clear!
-Clear!

967
01:20:17,563 --> 01:20:20,565
Command post, two officers down.

968
01:20:20,942 --> 01:20:22,275
-Clear!
-Clear!

969
01:20:23,194 --> 01:20:24,569
Lecter's gone, Sarge.

970
01:20:24,612 --> 01:20:26,446
The prisoner is missing.

971
01:20:26,531 --> 01:20:28,448
Boyle's gun is gone, Sergeant.

972
01:20:28,533 --> 01:20:31,076
Repeat. Lecter is missing and armed.

973
01:20:31,202 --> 01:20:34,246
He stripped the bed.
Might be making a rope.

974
01:20:34,330 --> 01:20:35,998
Check all windows.

975
01:20:36,082 --> 01:20:38,417
Where the fuck is my ambulance?

976
01:20:39,085 --> 01:20:40,502
He's alive.

977
01:20:41,212 --> 01:20:43,255
Sergeant Tate, he's alive!

978
01:20:43,798 --> 01:20:46,925
Get a hold of him where you can
feel his hands, son. Talk to him.

979
01:20:47,427 --> 01:20:48,677
What do I say?

980
01:20:48,761 --> 01:20:51,555
It's Jim Pembry! Now talk to him, damn it!

981
01:20:52,557 --> 01:20:54,683
Lecter is missing and armed.

982
01:20:54,851 --> 01:20:57,102
Pembry. Pembry, can you hear me?

983
01:20:57,186 --> 01:21:00,188
He took Boyle's gun.
Pembry got off one round.

984
01:21:00,273 --> 01:21:02,274
There's a chance Lecter was hit.

985
01:21:02,358 --> 01:21:04,443
Keep breathing in and out. That's it.

986
01:21:04,527 --> 01:21:07,779
You're doing a good job.
You look real good there.

987
01:21:08,531 --> 01:21:11,408
Yeah, you look... You look real good.

988
01:21:28,634 --> 01:21:29,760
-You ready?
-Let's go.

989
01:21:29,802 --> 01:21:31,720
-Let's do it.
-Let's go.

990
01:21:42,815 --> 01:21:44,983
Looking good, Pembry.
You're gonna make it.

991
01:21:45,068 --> 01:21:47,152
You're just fine. You're doing all right.
That's right.

992
01:21:47,236 --> 01:21:49,654
-Okay, I need that IV now.
-Lactated ringers.

993
01:21:49,739 --> 01:21:50,989
Can we get the strap?

994
01:21:51,074 --> 01:21:52,115
Where's the fucking oxygen?

995
01:21:52,158 --> 01:21:53,909
-Looking good, buddy. That's right.
-Bob!

996
01:21:53,993 --> 01:21:55,827
Stay with me. Stay with me here.

997
01:21:57,497 --> 01:21:59,706
We're losing him. Downstairs. Take him!

998
01:22:00,500 --> 01:22:01,708
And up!

999
01:22:03,294 --> 01:22:04,419
-Elevator!
-Out of the way!

1000
01:22:04,504 --> 01:22:06,004
Out of the way!

1001
01:22:10,843 --> 01:22:12,177
CP to Tate.

1002
01:22:12,887 --> 01:22:15,097
Roger, Lieutenant. Tate here.

1003
01:22:15,807 --> 01:22:18,642
I'm on the elevator bringing Pembry down.

1004
01:22:18,893 --> 01:22:20,936
He seems to be hanging on.

1005
01:22:21,562 --> 01:22:23,563
Top three floors secured.

1006
01:22:24,190 --> 01:22:26,108
